{"id": "EUVD-2025-9348", "enisaUuid": "78d893b7-2135-358e-a885-df7a7f440ec8", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nnet: mctp: unshare packets when reassembling\n\nEnsure that the frag_list used for reassembly isn't shared with other\npackets. This avoids incorrect reassembly when packets are cloned, and\nprevents a memory leak due to circular references between fragments and\ntheir skb_shared_info.\n\nThe upcoming MCTP-over-USB driver uses skb_clone which can trigger the\nproblem - other MCTP drivers don't share SKBs.\n\nA kunit test is added to reproduce the issue.", "datePublished": "2025-04-01T18:30:54", "dateUpdated": "2025-10-31T21:30:53", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/5c47d5bfa7b096cf8890afac32141c578583f8e0", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/f44fff3d3c6cd67b6f348b821d73c4d6888c7a6e", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/f5d83cf0eeb90fade4d5c4d17d24b8bee9ceeecc", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-21972"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-21972"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "1aaccc7d-ab58-3dd9-b8e5-62d3698d3bc1", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5.15"}, {"id": "5783b147-dcff-3517-a12d-fa1d1ef1bc76", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": ""}, {"id": "601e65b2-731e-381f-b68e-9c5301eb8d1f", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "4a992bbd365094730a31bae1e12a6ca695336d57 <f44fff3d3c6cd67b6f348b821d73c4d6888c7a6e"}, {"id": "7c781cf6-449c-38c4-84b1-d8fbe4d95ca0", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "4a992bbd365094730a31bae1e12a6ca695336d57 <5c47d5bfa7b096cf8890afac32141c578583f8e0"}, {"id": "ff182037-7fce-3c61-8714-55036a7d903a", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "4a992bbd365094730a31bae1e12a6ca695336d57 <f5d83cf0eeb90fade4d5c4d17d24b8bee9ceeecc"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "5783b147-dcff-3517-a12d-fa1d1ef1bc76", "vendor": {"name": "Linux"}}], "isExploited": false}